    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-09-24T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-09-24T16:00:00-05:00" n="342"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d342">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A15 Arms Truce/39: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-09-24T22:00:00+01:00"
                            >September 24, 1931—10 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received September 24—8:45 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>162. At meeting of the Third Committee this afternoon Madariaga declared that
                    while his Government was prepared to vote in favor of any proposal which the
                    Committee would accept unanimously he would suggest as a more farsighted and
                    elastic measure a proposal whereby the Assembly should recommend to all nations
                    participating in the Disarmament Conference a 10 per cent budgetary reduction on
                    armament expenditures covering the period of 1 year.</p>
                <pb facs="0570" n="456" xml:id="pg_456"/>
                <p>In view of our previous attitude on budgetary limitation<note n="63"
                        xml:id="d342fn63">For the attitude of the United States on budgetary
                        limitation as expressed in the Preparatory Commission for the Disarmament
                        Conference, see, for example, <ref target="frus1926v01#pg_94">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1926, vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">i</hi>, pp. 94</ref>–<ref
                            target="frus1926v01#pg_95">95</ref> and <ref target="frus1926v01#pg_97"
                            >97</ref>–<ref target="frus1926v01#pg_98">98</ref>; and <ref
                            target="frus1927v01#pg_172">
                            <hi rend="italic">ibid.</hi>, 1927, vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">i</hi>,
                            pp. 172</ref>–<ref target="frus1927v01#pg_173">173</ref>.</note> unless
                    I receive instructions to the contrary I shall maintain entire reserve if this
                    proposal takes the form of a resolution.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
